quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  40,78,"We sent Messengers before thee; of some We have related to thee, and some We have not related to thee. It was not for any Messenger to bring a sign, save by God's leave. When God's command comes, justly the issue shall be decided; then the vain-doers shall be lost"
  40,79,"It is God who appointed for you the cattle, some of them to ride and of some you eat"
  40,80,"other uses also you have in them; and that on them you may attain a need in your breasts, and upon them and on the ships you are carried"
  40,81,And He shows you His signs; then which of God's signs do you reject
  40,82,"What, have they not journeyed in the land and beheld how was the end of those before them? They were stronger than themselves in might and left firmer traces in the earth; yet that they earned did not avail them"
  40,83,"So, when their Messengers brought them the clear signs, they rejoiced in what knowledge they had, and were encompassed by that they mocked at"
  40,84,"Then, when they saw Our might, they said, 'We believe in God alone, and we disbelieve in that we were associating with Him"
  40,85,"But their belief when they saw Our might did not profit them -- the wont of God, as in the past, touching His servants; then the unbelievers shall be lost"